description.en: Bitcoin is the first successful internet money based on peer-to-peer technology; whereby no central bank or authority is involved in the transaction and production of the Bitcoin currency. It was created by an anonymous individual/group under the name, Satoshi Nakamoto. The source code is available publicly as an open source project, anybody can look at it and be part of the developmental process. Bitcoin is changing the way we see money as we speak. The idea was to produce a means of exchange, independent of any central authority, that could be transferred electronically in a secure, verifiable and immutable way. It is a decentralized peer-to-peer internet currency making mobile payment easy, very low transaction fees, protects your identity, and it works anywhere all the time with no central authority and banks. Bitcoin is designed to have only 21 million BTC ever created, thus making it a deflationary currency. Bitcoin uses the SHA-256 hashing algorithm with an average transaction confirmation time of 10 minutes. Miners today are mining Bitcoin using ASIC chip dedicated to only mining Bitcoin, and the hash rate has shot up to peta hashes. Being the first successful online cryptography currency, Bitcoin has inspired other alternative currencies such as Litecoin, Peercoin, Primecoin, and so on. The cryptocurrency then took off with the innovation of the turing-complete smart contract by Ethereum which led to the development of other amazing projects such as EOS, Tron, and even crypto-collectibles such as CryptoKitties.

Bitcoin is a digital currency created by Satoshi Nakamoto in 2009, with a structure in which there is no central device for issuing and managing currencies. Instead, Bitcoin's transactions are made by a P2P-based distributed database, and trades are based on a public key cryptographic basis. Bitcoin has disclosure. Bitcoin is stored in the form of a wallet file, each of which is given a unique address, and based on that address, Bitcoin's transactions are made. Bitcoin is one of the first implementations of the cryptocurrency that Waitay posted on the cyberpunk mailing list in 1998.

bitcoin is the first virtualization implemented. Without the central power or middleman managing issuance and distribution, users participating in the network using P2P network technology are subject to issuing currency and jointly managing transfer applications. It is Bitcoin that first introduced the blockchain technology that made it possible. The number of individuals and businesses using

Bitcoin is a new social phenomenon, but it is growing very quickly. Based on this, value increase, as well as millions of dollars of bitcoin are exchanged every day. 

 Bitcoin is currently the largest in circulation and the largest in coins in the virtualized market, and the volume is also stable. Ethereum is chasing quickly, but you can still see it as the most robust virtualization. 

coin feature
1.Bitcoin's operating system, in which trade-offs can be managed by these users without a central subject, is attributed to blockchain technology. Blockchain operates in a way that recognizes only the same content by sharing books as easy to say and comparing book files that are always on each other's computers. Thus, security is achieved through the opposite of the strong defense of access to the ledger in traditional financial institutions. Hacking a ledger requires manipulating a 51% ledger at the same time, which is virtually impossible. Because, it takes a lot of computing power to run it, and this is because possible supercomputers do not exist in the world. In addition, the materials in the ledger are stored in blocks in the form of cryptographic hashes, not recorded in joules, and these blocks are connected to each other, providing stronger security. 

2. Bitcoin issues a new coin in a way that pays the miner for the block issuance compensation. Block coverage is halved based on every 210,000 blocks (about 4 years). Initially, 50 bitcoin was issued, and it continues to decline in half every four years. When the total amount of coins reaches 21 million, the new issuance will end, after which the system will be supported only through transaction fees. 

 core value
